[According to the data on the Worldometer website, the total number of cases of COVID-19 worldwide is now 307 037, with 81 054 cases reported by China. There are now a total of 225 983 confirmed cases of COVID-19 reported from 187 countries/locations outside mainland China representing an increase of 31 250 cases when compared with the data on 20 Mar 2020, with Italy accounting for 6557 of the newly reported cases, the USA for 6590 cases, and Spain for 3986 of newly reported cases, The total number of confirmed cases reported from outside of China now represents 73.6% of the total number of reported cases. The epicenter has shifted outside of China to Western Europe and the USA is accelerating rapidly as more testing has become available. A global total of 13 069 deaths have been reported, 9808 outside mainland China.

For the 24th consecutive day, more cases have been reported from outside mainland China than within mainland China. The total number of deaths reported from outside of mainland China is now greater than the total number of deaths reported by mainland China. Mainland China went 3 days without any locally transmitted cases until today (21 Mar 2020) when there was a positive case associated with contact with an imported case; South Korea has slowly decreased daily new case counts hovering in the 100 plus or minus 50 cases. Cases in the USA are escalating very rapidly and Europe's rise is equally daunting. It would be interesting to see an epidemic curve by date of onset to see what the true curve of transmission is, as I suspect now that more testing is being done, many of those tested have been sick for days awaiting testing. - Mod.MPP]

