and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[The big news, this is now day 4 with no newly confirmed, locally acquired cases in Wuhan or Hubei province, China in the past 24 hours, but there is a mysterious single case that was reported from outside of Hubei. There are 46 newly confirmed cases reported to have been confirmed in the past 24 hours, 45 of whom are importations from overseas travel, but there is one addition with no information provided. A media report (http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/a/202003/22/WS5e76c9cfa310128217280fca.html) mentions that the case was from Guangdong province and was epidemiologically linked to a recent imported case. The location of origin of the original imported case was not specified, but the imported cases from 21 Mar 2020 came from UK, Thailand, Spain, France, the Philippines, and Turkey.

According to the report above, a total of 81 054 cases of confirmed COVID-19 have now been reported from mainland China, representing an increase of 46 cases in the past 24 hours since yesterday's (20 Mar 2020) report was prepared. In addition, 6 deaths were reported, 5 (83.3%) of them in Hubei province. 48 new cases were reported from Hong Kong, which bears watching as the cases have been slowly but steadily climbing. Macau reported no additional newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours.

Of the 46 newly confirmed cases, 45 were imported cases into China representing 97.8% of all reported cases in the past 24 hours. Cases were reported by Guangdong (7), Beijing (13), Shanghai (14), Fujian (4), 2 each in Jiangsu, and one each in Hebei, Zhejiang, Jiangxi, Shandong, and Sichuan, bringing the total number of imported cases to 314.

A map of China showing provinces can be seen at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map is available at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=7124533,155 - Mod.MPP]

